# Sentinel Phase 2: API Endpoints, WebSocket, & SDK

## Goal

Build the missing dashboard-ready API endpoints, add real-time WebSocket event streaming, and create a lightweight `@sentinel/sdk` npm package for client integration.

---

## Phase 1: Missing API Endpoints

### 1.1 Stats Endpoint

> [!NOTE]
> This provides the dashboard overview — total counts, severity breakdown, avg confidence.

#### [NEW] [stats.helpers.ts](file:///d:/Sentinel/src/services/incident-service/src/helpers/stats.helpers.ts)

Query service that runs aggregate queries on `incidents`, `alerts`, `policy_logs`:

```typescript
class StatsService {
  getDashboardStats() → {
    totalIncidents, openCount, resolvedCount, criticalCount,
    avgConfidence, totalAlerts, unacknowledgedAlerts,
    totalPolicyViolations, severityBreakdown: {low, medium, high, critical},
    recentTrend: [{date, count}]  // last 7 days
  }
}
```

