## Phase 2: WebSocket Real-Time Updates

### Architecture

The gateway will host a Socket.io server alongside Express. Services communicate events via Kafka → the gateway's own Kafka consumer picks them up and broadcasts to connected WebSocket clients.

```
Firewall/Incident Service → Kafka → Gateway Kafka Consumer → Socket.io → Dashboard Client
```

#### [NEW] [gateway/src/websocket/socketServer.ts](file:///d:/Sentinel/src/gateway/src/websocket/socketServer.ts)

```typescript
import { Server } from "socket.io";
import http from "http";

export const initSocketServer = (httpServer: http.Server) => {
  const io = new Server(httpServer, { cors: { origin: "*" } });

  io.on("connection", (socket) => {
    console.log(`Dashboard client connected: ${socket.id}`);
    socket.on("disconnect", () => console.log(`Client disconnected: ${socket.id}`));
  });

  return io;
};
```

#### [NEW] [gateway/src/websocket/realtimeConsumer.ts](file:///d:/Sentinel/src/gateway/src/websocket/realtimeConsumer.ts)

A Kafka consumer in the gateway that subscribes to key topics and emits Socket.io events:

| Kafka Topic | Socket.io Event | Payload |
|---|---|---|
| `incident.created` | `incident:created` | `{ tempId, traceId, source, severity }` |
| `incident.analyzed` | `incident:analyzed` | `{ incidentId, traceId, summary, confidence }` |
| `alert.created` | `alert:created` | `{ incident_id, severity, message }` |
| `policy.violation` | `policy:violation` | `{ tempId, traceId, violations[] }` |

#### [MODIFY] [gateway/src/index.ts](file:///d:/Sentinel/src/gateway/src/index.ts)

Change from `app.listen()` to `http.createServer(app)` so Socket.io can attach:

```typescript
import http from "http";
import { initSocketServer } from "./websocket/socketServer";
import { startRealtimeConsumer } from "./websocket/realtimeConsumer";

const server = http.createServer(app);
const io = initSocketServer(server);
startRealtimeConsumer(io);  // Kafka → WebSocket bridge
server.listen(PORT);
```

#### Dependencies to add to gateway:
```bash
npm install socket.io kafkajs
npm install -D @types/socket.io
```

